<br>
     As you know I have begun to aggressivly work on the non planar parts of my epic quest.  I am posting this here to ask if anyone is willing and available to go and kill Capt Rottgrime with me in the overthere.  I have pasted a post for a pull and battle plan below to help with this request.  I would need a monk, (or someone who can FD) who would not be Kos to the outpost.  I am told agnostic monks work well.  This would be just for the pull.  Or as suggested below we could possibly get a mage with CoH to help us with the pull.  As listed below this should be dooable by 12 peeps, however the battle plan below states that this was overkill.  I will be on tonight at 9:30pm est if this is dooable tonight.  If not tis cool as I understand this is the first day its posted hehe.  Any night after 8pm est would be great.(if thats cool for other guidies)  Also im pretty sure that I can get Mojomon, a lvl 59 mage with CoH to help with the protection of the puller if we have no agnostic monk available.  So whaddya guys think eh?  8-)  <br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for considering the request<br>
Rasa Ghoull<br>
42 Magician<br>
Knights of Freedom<br>
<br>
DA BATTLE PLAN<br>
&quot;Ok, most will never need to know this, but if one person finds it useful, it's not a waste of time.<br>
<br>
Part of the insanely hard magician epic quest involves killing Captain Rottgrime in the outpost in Overthere. He is a level 55 skeleton, and doesn't seem to be too tough to kill.<br>
<br>
The trick is pulling him. Capt. Rottgrime is surrounded by 6 or 8 skeletons, all blue to me at 52 (someone said lvl 50, but I'm not sure). Besides that, there is a damn hard 55 or so Golems guarding both side entrances, and 4 gargoyles, level 50-53 or so guarding the main entrance. And still, you have about 4 roaming DE goons, as well as General D'Veers who's tough as nails and a necro. Add to this the fact that most are KOS in the outpost, and it's not a pretty sight.<br>
<br>
The pull is actually not that hard. First off, you're probably going to want someone who is not KOS to pull him...Agnostic monks work nicely. My faction in the outpost was kindly, so I can roam freely. You need at least one other non kos person to help, and they dont' necessarily have to have FD. We had a troll warrior.<br>
<br>
Have your groups set up camp on the northwest wall, very near the outpost. Very few roamers, and no goons seem to come up that way. We had 2 groups: 2 clerics, 2 magicians, 1 monk, 1 warrior, 2 necros, 1 druid, 1 shaman (turned out to be overkill), and an enchanter showed up a bit later.<br>
<br>
Get in to the outpost, and target rottgrime..stand as far back while still in shuriken range as possible. A great thing to have here is one of those nice snaring nets from Crystal Caverns. Have your lookout watch the golem on the far east side of the outpost, and when he is at his point closest to water, either cast snare net or chuck a shuriken at the captain, turn, and run like hell. If you happen to get stunned, use stone stance. Then run outside the outpost, well outside the gates, then FD. Those things hit hard, but never took more than a bubble or so, even with about 10 on my tail. Have your lookout/tagger run up to Rottgrim and start hailing him. 99% of the time, this will stop him, while everyone else walks back. Either /q to clear aggro, or have your mage CoTH you back, then run back up to capt, or have lookout pull him the rest of the way.<br>
<br>
Bang snap pow, easy kill, happy mage. We did it twice, 0 deaths. Faction is rough though...I went from kindly to indifferent in 4 kills (2 capt, 2 goons). And on that note, for some reason a goon always managed to find us and show up with the captain...not a big deal, except for the additional faction hit. The only other advice I can give is to know where the goons are; they leave the outpost at midnight and usually come back or despawn at 10am if memory serves. Try to time it when they are furthest away.<br>
<br>
I wrote this for one reason: I asked 3 people about pulling this, and they either said it was impossible to split all those guys, or said to have a cleric with a click stick handy. There are other tactics; some have bards kiting the stuff around and a tagger to pull rottgrime, etc..but this was so clean and fast, seems like a waste of time any other way.&quot;<br>
